What you need to know:

NOC-K President Paul Tergat and Kenya’s Chef de Mission to the Tokyo Olympics, Waithaka Kioni, along with Anti-Doping Agency of Kenya chief executive Japhter Rugut along with heads of Sports Kenya, Kenya Academy of Sports and senior Ministry of Sports Culture and Heritage officials are among those in attendance.Besides studying recommendations from the Rio Probe Committee presented by the committee’s chairman Paul Ochieng, the retreat group will also study issues around the Tokyo Olympics accreditation, local and international pre-Olympic training camps and travel preparations.